href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The pointwise sum <fr:tex>M+N</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>M,N \in \mathrm {Mat}_{ \mathbb {B} } { \mathopen {} \left ( m , n \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> corresponds to the union of the <fr:link
href="jms-00IZ.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IZ">relations associated</fr:link> to <fr:tex>M</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>N</fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _{ \mathbb {B}} { \mathopen {} \left ( M+N \right ) \mathclose {}}  =   \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _{ \mathbb {B}}M  \cup   \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _{ \mathbb {B}}N </fr:tex><fr:p>Moreover, the <fr:link
href="jms-00JP.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00JP">zero matrix</fr:link> corresponds to the <fr:link
href="jms-00IG.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IG">empty relation</fr:link>: <fr:tex>\operatorname { \underline {rel}} _{ \mathbb {B}} \mathbf {0} =  \varnothing</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
